@startuml
title SupportBot - System Context

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #4b5563
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.2
skinparam RectangleBorderColor #1f2937
skinparam RectangleBackgroundColor #f8fafc
skinparam PackageBorderColor #1f2937
skinparam PackageBackgroundColor #eef2ff
skinparam DatabaseBorderColor #1f2937
skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #ecfeff
skinparam ActorBorderColor #1f2937
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #fef3c7

actor "Telegram User" as TelegramUser
actor "Support Manager" as SupportManager
rectangle "Telegram Bot API" as TelegramApi

package "SupportBot" as SupportBot {
  rectangle "support-admin\nNext.js admin dashboard" as SupportAdmin
  rectangle "telegram-webhook\nSupabase Edge Function" as TelegramWebhook
  database "Supabase Postgres\npublic.messages" as MessagesDb
}

rectangle "Supabase Platform" as SupabasePlatform

TelegramUser --> TelegramApi : sends support message
TelegramApi --> TelegramWebhook : forwards webhook update
TelegramWebhook --> MessagesDb : persists inbound message
TelegramWebhook --> TelegramApi : sends acknowledgement

SupportManager --> SupportAdmin : opens dashboard
SupportAdmin --> MessagesDb : reads message history

TelegramWebhook --> SupabasePlatform : deployed on
MessagesDb --> SupabasePlatform : hosted by
SupportAdmin --> SupabasePlatform : uses project URL and anon key

@enduml
